The National Secretary of All Progressives Grand Alliance (APGA), Mr. Labaran Maku, has returned to the Peoples Democratic Party (PDP). Maku, a former Minister of Information in ex-President Goodluck Jonathan’s administration, confirmed this to the News Agency of Nigeria (NAN) yesterday in Lafia, the Nasarawa State capital.   Who becomes next Kaduna governor?     13 aspirants eyeing Niger Government House     Jedy-Agba to vie for Obudu/Obanliku/Bekwara Federal…   He said his decision to return to the PDP was in response to the yearnings of his people in Nasarawa State. NAN reports that Maku had defected from the PDP to APGA in 2015 after his unsuccessful attempt to clinch the PDP governorship ticket. The former minister contested for the Nasarawa State governorship position in 2015 and 2019 on the APGA ticket.